The paper deals with languages of infinite words, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). It also involves the use of regular expressions and automata, which are fundamental concepts in automata theory (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the decidability of a logic that extends monadic second-order logic, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
